prompt: Give an example of a tree. Answer concisely in one paragraph.
output: A tree is a plant that has a trunk, branches and leaves. An example of a tree would be the oak tree which has a strong trunk, many branches and green leaves. The oak tree also produces acorns as fruit. It can grow to be very large and live for hundreds of years. Oak trees are commonly found in forests and woodlands across the world. They provide habitat for many animals and help to maintain healthy ecosystems.
